subject:

GOD AT WORK THROUGH THE WORD (Mk. 4:26-29)
===================================================================
verse:

The seed sprouts and grows, … first the stalk, then the
head, Then the full kernel in the head. (Mk. 4:27-28)

===================================================================
reflection:

Seeds contain enormous power. Sown into the ground these
little “workers” take of their jackets and get busy. New
plants emerge and mature. We can prepare the soil, fertilize
it, irrigate, and sow the seeds. But that is all we can do.
We cannot put the germinating power into the seed itself.
That is the way it is with the Word of God, the Gospel of
Jesus Christ. As Christians we proclaim it in our
neighborhoods and to the world at large. We prepare
ourselves, speak words people can understand, use the media
at our disposal, and the like. But there is a limit to what
we can do. When it comes to producing results in
people—creating the saving, heart changing faith—we can do
nothing at all. “No man can redeem the life of another or
give God a ransom for him” (Ps. 49:7). The Gospel has
wonderful Power “ for the salvation of everyone who
believes” (Ro. 1:16). It is the Triune God who effects our
salvation.

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord God, You are the Triune God-Father, Son, and Holy
Spirit-working perfectly in unity to bring about our
salvation. Just as seeds hold the power to grow, Your Word
and the Gospel carry the power to bring new life through
faith. We prepare the soil and proclaim the Gospel, but only
You can create saving faith in the hearts of people. Thank
You for the work of the Father who chose us, the Son who
redeemed us, and the Spirit who regenerates and applies
salvation. May we trust fully in Your Triune power to save
and sustain us. Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
